  "elapsed_s": 6.5,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "My family, [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] we were lucky except my father was caught, and he was beaten up pretty badly.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- but he got home somehow.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Why my father was caught-- this is going back already.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I have to go back with a story.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] The-- the Russians, the KGB at that time was called NKVD.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And their building, where their-- in their headquarters, in the basement, when the Germans came in, they found about 40 Poles and Ukrainians killed.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And that was, again, part of the-- of the permission given to the Ukrainians to take-- to-- to kill the Jews, because they blamed the Jews for everything.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Every Jew was a communist.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] At that time, they grabbed my father.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "He should go and make caskets for those people that were killed by the Russians.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And then late in the afternoon, somehow he was going home from wherever he was working, and they caught him.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "They beat him up.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "But they let him go, and he got home.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And we survived at first pogrom.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, my father was clean shaved, modern dressed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "We had no-- as matter of fact, in the whole my family, some of them were very religious, but none of them were-- [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] wore Hasidic clothes or anything like that.",
      "word_count": 34
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, what we felt at that time was fear-- fear on the-- about the unknown, fear of not knowing what's going to happen, how are we going to live.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And-- and after a few days, when they buried the Jewish [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] people that were killed-- that we still had a cemetery, and they were buried in the Jewish cemetery in town.",
      "word_count": 35
    }
  ],
